{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Mat|8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","chapter":8,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":1,"text":"When he came down from the mountain, large crowds followed him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":2,"text":"Right away a man with leprosy came up and knelt before him, saying, “Lord, if you are willing, you can make me clean.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":3,"text":"Reaching out his hand, Jesus touched him, saying, “I am willing; be made clean.” Immediately his leprosy was cleansed.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":4,"text":"Then Jesus told him, “See that you don’t tell anyone; but go, show yourself to the priest, and offer the gift that Moses commanded, as a testimony to them.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":5,"text":"When he entered Capernaum, a centurion came to him, pleading with him,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":6,"text":"“Lord, my servant is lying at home paralyzed, in terrible agony.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":7,"text":"He said to him, “Am I to come and heal him?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":8,"text":"“Lord,” the centurion replied, “I am not worthy to have you come under my roof. But just say the word, and my servant will be healed.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":9,"text":"For I too am a man under authority, having soldiers under my command. I say to this one, ‘Go,’ and he goes; and to another, ‘Come,’ and he comes; and to my servant, ‘Do this!’ and he does it.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":10,"text":"Hearing this, Jesus was amazed and said to those following him, “Truly I tell you, I have not found anyone in Israel with so great a faith.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":11,"text":"I tell you that many will come from east and west to share the banquet with Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob in the kingdom of heaven.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":12,"text":"But the sons of the kingdom will be thrown into the outer darkness where there will be weeping and gnashing of teeth.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":13,"text":"Then Jesus told the centurion, “Go. As you have believed, let it be done for you.” And his servant was healed that very moment.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":14,"text":"Jesus went into Peter’s house and saw his mother-in-law lying in bed with a fever.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":15,"text":"So he touched her hand, and the fever left her. Then she got up and began to serve him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":16,"text":"When evening came, they brought to him many who were demon-possessed. He drove out the spirits with a word and healed all who were sick,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":17,"text":"so that what was spoken through the prophet Isaiah might be fulfilled:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":18,"text":"When Jesus saw a large crowd around him, he gave the order to go to the other side of the sea.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":19,"text":"A scribe approached him and said, “Teacher, I will follow you wherever you go.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":20,"text":"Jesus told him, “Foxes have dens, and birds of the sky have nests, but the Son of Man has no place to lay his head.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":21,"text":"“Lord,” another of his disciples said, “first let me go bury my father.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":22,"text":"But Jesus told him, “Follow me, and let the dead bury their own dead.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":23,"text":"As he got into the boat, his disciples followed him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":24,"text":"Suddenly, a violent storm arose on the sea, so that the boat was being swamped by the waves —but Jesus kept sleeping.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:25","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":25,"text":"So the disciples came and woke him up, saying, “Lord, save us! We’re going to die!”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:26","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":26,"text":"He said to them, “Why are you afraid, you of little faith?” Then he got up and rebuked the winds and the sea, and there was a great calm.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:27","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":27,"text":"The men were amazed and asked, “What kind of man is this? Even the winds and the sea obey him!”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:28","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":28,"text":"When he had come to the other side, to the region of the Gadarenes, two demon-possessed men met him as they came out of the tombs. They were so violent that no one could pass that way.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:29","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":29,"text":"Suddenly they shouted, “What do you have to do with us, Son of God? Have you come here to torment us before the time?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:30","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":30,"text":"A long way off from them, a large herd of pigs was feeding.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:31","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":31,"text":"“If you drive us out,” the demons begged him, “send us into the herd of pigs.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:32","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":32,"text":"“Go!” he told them. So when they had come out, they entered the pigs, and the whole herd rushed down the steep bank into the sea and perished in the water.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:33","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":33,"text":"Then the men who tended them fled. They went into the city and reported everything, especially what had happened to those who were demon-possessed.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:34","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":8,"verse":34,"text":"At that, the whole town went out to meet Jesus. When they saw him, they begged him to leave their region.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","chapter":8,"paragraphStarts":[1,3,5,7,8,10,14,18,20,21,22,23,26,27,28,30,32],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"A Man Cleansed"},{"beforeVerse":5,"text":"A Centurion’s Faith"},{"beforeVerse":14,"text":"Healings at Capernaum"},{"beforeVerse":18,"text":"The Cost of Following Jesus"},{"beforeVerse":23,"text":"Wind and Waves Obey Jesus"},{"beforeVerse":28,"text":"Demons Driven Out by Jesus"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"When he came down from the mountain, large crowds "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 5:1","book":"Mat","chapter":5,"verse":1,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 3:7","book":"Luk","chapter":3,"verse":7,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" followed him. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Mt 5:1","book":"Mat","chapter":5,"verse":1},{"label":"Lk 3:7","book":"Luk","chapter":3,"verse":7}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:8:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Right away "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 1:40–44","book":"Mrk","chapter":1,"verse":40,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 5:12–14","book":"Luk","chapter":5,"verse":12,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" a man with leprosy "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Gk lepros; a term for various skin diseases, also in v. 3; see Lv 13–14"},{"kind":"text","text":" came up and knelt before him, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 9:18","book":"Mat","chapter":9,"verse":18,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 15:25","book":"Mat","chapter":15,"verse":25,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 18:26","book":"Mat","chapter":18,"verse":26,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 20:20","book":"Mat","chapter":20,"verse":20,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jn 9:38","book":"Jhn","chapter":9,"verse":38,"letter":"g"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 10:25","book":"Act","chapter":10,"verse":25,"letter":"h"},{"kind":"text","text":" saying, “Lord, if you are willing, you can make me clean.”"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Mk 1:40–44","book":"Mrk","chapter":1,"verse":40},{"label":"Lk 5:12–14","book":"Luk","chapter":5,"verse":12},{"label":"Mt 9:18","book":"Mat","chapter":9,"verse":18},{"label":"Mt 